# These tests have been added here since upstream Prometheus has recently
# added support for smoothed/anchored histograms.
# These tests will be removed once our Mimir implementation is completed.

load 1m
  mixed 1 2 3 {{schema:0 sum:5 count:4 buckets:[1 2 1]}} 4 5 6 7+1x60

# MQE-only: when the boundary-aligned anchored range puts the histogram exactly at rangeEnd
# (t=3m here), Prometheus's engine drops the series entirely, while MQE returns {} 0 because the
# resulting buffer has only a single histogram sample with no float reset partner. The float
# samples in the original window are removed by anchored boundary mutation (lookback float at
# rangeStart is consumed as the synthetic anchor, no float remains in (rangeStart, rangeEnd]).
eval instant at 3m resets(mixed[1m] anchored)
  {} 0
